n -m pytest backend/tests/test_session_service.py backend/tests/test_session_api.py`, `npm run lint`, `npm run build`, and `npm run test`. Browser QA captured [prompt-22-workspace-desktop.png](/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/.artifacts/webapp-qa/prompt-22-workspace-desktop.png) and [prompt-22-workspace-mobile.png](/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/.artifacts/webapp-qa/prompt-22-workspace-mobile.png); the desktop chat pane measured `0.328` of the shell width, and mobile stacked cleanly. The only verification limit was a pre-existing compose backend blocker from the local `secrets.yaml` schema, so the browser run used intercepted API responses against the live Vite app instead of a fully live backend container.\n./prompts/19-data-layer-integration-tests.yolopilot.md:3234:          context: ../../tools/webapp-qa\n./prompts/19-data-layer-integration-tests.yolopilot.md:3238:        working_dir: /workspace/tools/webapp-qa\n./prompts/19-data-layer-integration-tests.yolopilot.md:3240:          PUPPETEER_EXECUTABLE_PATH: /usr/bin/chromium\n./prompts/19-data-layer-integration-tests.yolopilot.md:3244:          - webapp_qa_node_modules:/workspace/tools/webapp-qa/node_modules\n./prompts/28-error-loading-and-feedback-states.summary.md:210:### Browser and screenshot verification\n./prompts/28-error-loading-and-feedback-states.summary.md:212:I used the repo\u2019s bundled browser QA flow and captured the following screenshots:\n./prompts/28-error-loading-and-feedback-states.summary.md:214:- `/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/.artifacts/webapp-qa/prompt-28-home.png`\n./prompts/28-error-loading-and-feedback-states.summary.md:215:- `/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/.artifacts/webapp-qa/prompt-28-home-mobile.png`\n./prompts/28-error-loading-and-feedback-states.summary.md:216:- `/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/.artifacts/webapp-qa/prompt-28-workspace.png`\n./prompts/28-error-loading-and-feedback-states.summary.md:217:- `/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/.artifacts/webapp-qa/prompt-28-home-offline.png`\n./prompts/28-error-loading-and-feedback-states.summary.md:218:- `/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/.artifacts/webapp-qa/prompt-28-workspace-offline.png`\n./prompts/28-error-loading-and-feedback-states.summary.md:222:- `docker compose -f infra/compose/docker-compose.yml run --rm browser npm run check -- --spec /workspace/.artifacts/webapp-qa/prompt-28-home.spec.json`\n./prompts/28-error-loading-and-feedback-states.summary.md:223:- `docker compose -f infra/compose/docker-compose.yml run --rm browser npm run check -- --spec /workspace/.artifacts/webapp-qa/prompt-28-home-mobile.spec.json`\n./prompts/28-error-loading-and-feedback-states.summary.md:224:- `docker compose -f infra/compose/docker-compose.yml run --rm browser npm run check -- --spec /workspace/.artifacts/webapp-qa/prompt-28-workspace.spec.json`\n./prompts/28-error-loading-and-feedback-states.summary.md:225:- `docker exec storyteller-browser-1 sh -lc 'cd /workspace/tools/webapp-qa && npm run check -- --spec /workspace/.artifacts/webapp-qa/prompt-28-home-offline.spec.json'`\n./prompts/28-error-loading-and-feedback-states.summary.md:226:- `docker exec storyteller-browser-1 sh -lc 'cd /workspace/tools/webapp-qa && npm run check -- --spec /workspace/.artifacts/webapp-qa/prompt-28-workspace-offline.spec.json'`\n./prompts/28-error-loading-and-feedback-states.summary.md:244:- the normal-state workspace screenshot was captured before I took the backend down and shows the entrance transition slightly mid-fade in the top bar. The important new feedback banner and shell layout are still visible and readable.\n./prompts/28-error-loading-and-feedback-states.summary.md:255:This is not caused by the frontend changes in this prompt, but it prevented me from taking a refreshed post-restart workspace screenshot. The frontend code-level validation still passed, and the offline screenshots were captured successfully.\n./prompts/28-error-loading-and-feedback-states.summary.md:277:I first used `docker compose run --rm browser ...` for failure-mode screenshots. That was wrong because Compose eagerly recreated dependencies, including the backend I had intentionally stopped. I switched to `docker exec storyteller-browser-1 ...` against the already-running browser container, which preserved the real offline state.\n./prompts/22-workspace-two-pane-layout.codex.jsonlines:5:{\"type\":\"item.completed\",\"item\":{\"id\":\"item_1\",\"type\":\"command_execution\",\"command\":\"/bin/zsh -lc \\\"sed -n '1,220p' /Users/kevin/.codex/skills/odysseus-webapp-visual-qa/SKILL.md\\\"\",\"aggregated_output\":\"---\\nname: odysseus-webapp-visual-qa\\ndescription: Use when working on Odysseus webapp styling, layout, spacing, color, typography, or other visual-polish requests where live viewport screenshots should guide the work. Prefer this skill for most stylistic tweaks, verify changes against the running Docker Compose app, use the dedicated Odysseus screenshot CLI if it exists, and otherwise drive the app with Playwright and capture viewport screenshots.\\nmetadata:\\n  short-description: Screenshot-backed webapp styling workflow\\n---\\n\\n# Odysseus Webapp Visual QA\\n\\n## When To Use\\n\\n- Use for most stylistic tweaks in the Odysseus webapp: colors, spacing, typography, layout balance, pane sizing, header polish, card treatment, menu behavior, and responsive cleanup.\\n- Use when the user asks for screenshots, visual validation, UI polish, or requests that are best judged by looking at the rendered app instead of only reading code.\\n- Skip this skill for backend-only work unless the request also needs UI verification.\\n\\n## Core Workflow\\n\\n1. Check whether the repo has a dedicated Odysseus screenshot or browser-navigation CLI command.\\n- Prefer the dedicated `odysseus` command when it exists.\\n- Check with `odysseus --help` or inspect `/Users/kevin/code/odysseus/src/odysseus/cli.py`.\\n- If the dedicated command is absent, say so briefly in your own reasoning and use the Playwright fallback below.\\n\\n2. Reuse the Docker Compose app instead of starting a separate server.\\n- Check the stack with `docker compose ps --format json`.\\n- Treat `web` on `http://127.0.0.1:5173` and `api` on `http://127.0.0.1:8000` as the default local targets.\\n- Never spin up a separate Vite or FastAPI server just for visual QA when the Compose stack is available.\\n\\n3. If the Compose stack is down during Codex code-editing work, start it automatically in a Codex terminal.\\n- For Codex code-agent editing flows, do not stop to ask the user first.\\n- Start the stack in detached mode with `docker compose up -d`.\\n- Mention in an intermediary update that you started the stack because the visual QA workflow depends on the running app.\\n- Only pause and surface the issue if the compose start fails.\\n\\n4. Capture a baseline screenshot before editing when current visuals matter.\\n- Default to a desktop viewport of `1440x900`.\\n- Use a second narrow/mobile viewport when the change could affect responsiveness.\\n- Prefer viewport screenshots of the visible UI, not `fullPage`, unless the user specifically wants the entire scroll area.\\n\\n5. Navigate with stable selectors, then capture after edits.\\n- Prefer role, label, and visible-text selectors over brittle structure selectors.\\n- Wait for the relevant pane, menu, or state to settle before capture.\\n- Compare before and after screenshots from the same route and viewport.\\n\\n## Current Fallback When The Dedicated CLI Is Absent\\n\\nCheck whether Compose is running:\\n\\n```bash\\ndocker compose ps --format json\\n```\\n\\nStart it automatically for Codex editing runs when needed:\\n\\n```bash\\ndocker compose up -d\\n```\\n\\nTake a straight viewport screenshot:\\n\\n```bash\\ncd /Users/kevin/code/odysseus/webui && npx playwright screenshot --viewport-size=1440,900 http://127.0.0.1:5173 /tmp/odysseus-visual-qa.png\\n```\\n\\nFor scripted navigation, use a short task-specific Playwright script:\\n\\n```bash\\ncd /Users/kevin/code/odysseus/webui && node --input-type=module - <<'EOF'\\nimport { chromium } from \\\"playwright\\\";\\n\\nconst browser = await chromium.launch({ headless: true });\\nconst context = await browser.newContext({ viewport: { width: 1440, height: 900 } });\\nconst page = await context.newPage();\\n\\nawait page.goto(\\\"http://127.0.0.1:5173\\\");\\nawait page.getByRole(\\\"button\\\", { name: \\\"New Theme\\\" }).click();\\nawait page.screenshot({ path: \\\"/tmp/odysseus-visual-qa.png\\\" });\\n\\nawait browser.close();\\nEOF\\n```\\n\\n## Guidelines\\n\\n- Use live screenshots to decide whether a styling tweak is actually complete.\\n- Mention the exact screenshot path in the final response when you capture one.\\n- Prefer `/tmp/odysseus-visual-qa-*.png` for throwaway artifacts unless the user asked for a project artifact.\\n- For color, spacing, and hierarchy tweaks, compare before and after in the same viewport.\\n- For larger UI restyling, verify at least one desktop viewport and one narrow/mobile viewport.\\n- If the app fails to render or the screenshot workflow breaks, say exactly what blocked validation.\\n\",\"exit_code\":0,\"status\":\"completed\"}}\n./prompts/22-workspace-two-pane-layout.codex.jsonlines:7:{\"type\":\"item.completed\",\"item\":{\"id\":\"item_2\",\"type\":\"command_execution\",\"command\":\"/bin/zsh -lc \\\"rg --files /Users/kevin/code/storyteller | rg '(\\\"'^frontend/|package.json$|docker-compose|compose|vite|src/)'\\\"'\\\"\",\"aggregated_output\":\"/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/prompts/04-docker-compose-foundation.summary.md\\n/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/scripts/dev-compose.sh\\n/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/prompts/02-vite-react-scaffold.yolopilot.jsonlines\\n/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/prompts/02-vite-react-scaffold.summary.md\\n/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/prompts/02-vite-react-scaffold.yolopilot.md\\n/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/prompts/96-compose-dev-and-prod-shapes.md\\n/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/frontend/package.json\\n/U